Issues / Notes: quality control datum
label: quality control datum

Issues / Notes: quality control determination

label: no quality control issues identified datum
definition: A data item which is a statement confirming that quality control processes were carried out and no quality issues were detected.
alt definition: A statement confirming that quality control processes were carried out and no quality issues were detected.
comment: Example: This statement may be used in conjunction with the quality control determination statement "sequence passed quality control" to confirm that no issues were identified. It is possible that a sequence may pass QC but still have some issues worthy of noting e.g. novel indel detected. Note: quality control here refers to quality of the raw reads, consensus sequence or assembly, not the qaulity of analytical results e.g. lineage assignment.

label: sequence passed quality control datum
definition: A data item which is a statement confirming that quality control processes were carried out and that the sequence met the assessment criteria.
alt definition: A statement confirming that quality control processes were carried out and that the sequence met the assessment criteria.
comment: Example: Use this statement to indicate that quality control processes were carried out and that the sequence met the assessment criteria. Note: quality control here refers to quality of the raw reads, consensus sequence or assembly, not the qaulity of analytical results e.g. lineage assignment.

label: sequence failed quality control datum
definition: A data item which is a statement confirming that quality control processes were carried out and that the sequence did not meet the assessment criteria.
alt definition: A statement confirming that quality control processes were carried out and that the sequence did not meet the assessment criteria.
comment: Example: Use this statement to indicate that quality control processes were carried out and that the sequence failed to meet the assessment criteria. Note: quality control here refers to quality of the raw reads, consensus sequence or assembly, not the qaulity of analytical results e.g. lineage assignment.

label: minor quality control issues identified datum
definition: A data item which is a statement confirming that quality control processes were carried out and that the sequence did not meet the assessment criteria, however the issues detected were minor.
alt definition: A statement confirming that quality control processes were carried out and that the sequence did not meet the assessment criteria, however the issues detected were minor.
comment: Example: This statement may be used in conjunction with the quality control determination statement "sequence failed quality control" to communicate that the reasons why the sequence did not meet the assessment criteria. Minor issues may include phenomena that the analyst should review e.g. amplicons detected in the negative control sequence or more mutations than expected based on the reference sequence. The details of the issues can be described in the "quality control details" field. Note: quality control here refers to quality of the raw reads, consensus sequence or assembly, not the qaulity of analytical results e.g. lineage assignment.

label: sequence flagged for potential quality control issues datum
alternative label: sequence flagged for potential quality control issues
definition: A data item which is a statement confirming that quality control processes were carried out however it is unclear whether the sequence meets the assessment criteria and the assessment requires review.
alt definition: A statement confirming that quality control processes were carried out however it is unclear whether the sequence meets the assessment criteria and the assessment requires review.
comment: Example: This statement may be used in conjunction with other quality control determination statements to indicate potential sequence quality issues. Note: quality control here refers to quality of the raw reads, consensus sequence or assembly, not the qaulity of analytical results e.g. lineage assignment.

label: quality control not performed datum
definition: A data item which is a statement confirming that quality control processes have not been carried out.
alt definition: A statement confirming that quality control processes have not been carried out.
comment: Example: Use this statement to indicate that quality control processes have not been performed. Note: quality control here refers to quality of the raw reads, consensus sequence or assembly, not the qaulity of analytical results e.g. lineage assignment.

Issues / Notes: quality control issues

label: low quality sequence datum
definition: A data item that describes sequence data that does not meet quality control thresholds.
alt definition: Sequence data that does not meet quality control thresholds.

label: sequence contaminated datum
definition: A data item that describes sequence data that contains reads from unintended targets (e.g. other organisms, other samples) due to contamination so that it does not faithfully represent the genetic information from the biological source.
alt definition: Sequence data that contains reads from unintended targets (e.g. other organisms, other samples) due to contamination so that it does not faithfully represent the genetic information from the biological source.

label: low average genome coverage datum
definition: A data item that describes sequence data in which the entire length of the genome is not sufficiently sequenced (low breadth of coverage), or particular positions of the genome are not sequenced a prescribed number of times (low depth of coverage).
alt definition: Sequence data in which the entire length of the genome is not sufficiently sequenced (low breadth of coverage), or particular positions of the genome are not sequenced a prescribed number of times (low depth of coverage).

label: low percent genome captured datum
definition: A data item that describes sequence data in which the entire length of the genome is not sufficiently sequenced (low breadth of coverage).
alt definition: Sequence data in which the entire length of the genome is not sufficiently sequenced (low breadth of coverage).

label: read lengths shorter than expected datum
definition: A data item that describes average sequence read lengths that are below the expected size range given a particular sequencing instrument, reagents and conditions.
alt definition: Average sequence read lengths that are below the expected size range given a particular sequencing instrument, reagents and conditions.

label: sequence amplification artifacts datum
definition: A data item that describes sequence data containing errors generated during the polymerase chain reaction (PCR) amplification process during library generation (e.g. mutations, altered read distribution, amplicon dropouts).
alt definition: Sequence data containing errors generated during the PCR amplification process during library generation (e.g. mutations, altered read distribution, amplicon dropouts).

label: low signal to noise ratio datum
definition: A data item that describes sequence data containing more errors or undetermined bases (noise) than sequence representing the biological source (signal).
alt definition: Sequence data containing more errors or undetermined bases (noise) than sequence representing the biological source (signal).

label: low coverage of characteristic mutations datum
definition: A data item that describes sequence data that contains a lower than expected number of mutations that are usually observed in the reference sequence.
alt definition: Sequence data that contains a lower than expected number of mutations that are usually observed in the reference sequence.

label: cluster/outbreak investigation strategy
definition: A sampling strategy in which individuals are chosen for investigation into a disease cluster or outbreak.
editor note: Planned Obsolescence: this term is a placeholder for a term requested in another ontology. Once the appropriate ontology term is available, this term’s identifier will be obsoleted with a “term replaced by” id of the other term.
comment: The terms cluster and outbreak both describe the occurrence of new disease cases within a particular location and time period. The number of cases within a cluster are not necessarily greater than what is expected, however in an outbreak the number of cases does exceed the usual norm. In an outbreak the cases are confirmed to be epidemiologically linked while in a cluster an epidemiological connection is only suspected. Not all clusters are outbreaks, however each cluster needs to be investigated. [Source: https://covid19evidencereviews.saskhealthauthority.ca/en/permalink/coviddoc153]

Issues / Notes: exposure setting

Consulted with Damion and we decided a new term “exposure process” (GENEPIO:0100296) is a reasonable place to house these terms because some of these exposures are not specific to animals nor humans (which are the terms GENEPIO already has). I suggested moving the "animal" and "human" specific exposure processes as subclasses.
label: exposure process
definition: A process in which a recipient organism is exposed to a material entity.
Subclass label: animal exposure process|human to human exposure process
